Justification:
The FY2027 funding request for the Consolidated Afloat Networks and Enterprise Services (CANES) aligns with funding profile that supports the Navy's priority effort to modernize and protect tactical networks
against increased cyber threats and ensure operational readiness from competition to conflict. All procurements align with available ship platform (ship/submarine/shore) modernization windows and the
program's capacity to procure and install the product. Sufficient funding ensures that CANES is deployed to the Fleet as quickly as possible to mitigate obsolescence issues, cyber security threats, and keep
pace with increased computing and storage requirements for hosted mission applications, and support Department of War (DoW) directives to remove End of Life/Support (EOL/S) Windows Operating Systems
software (e.g., operating systems) from the Fleet as quickly as feasible. Obsolete Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) legacy hardware and the termination of cyber security support for legacy versions of COTS
software products (e.g., Microsoft, RedHat, Linux) drive increased sustainment costs, reduce operational availability and create critical cyber security vulnerabilities in Navy Tactical Networks. Replacing
these older networks and modernizing the tactical environment with CANES is the foundation for all Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (C4ISR)
investments to sustain functionality, interoperability, cyber security, supportability, and maintainability.

FY2027 - CANES funds are for the procurement of (6) Initial CANES Afloat units, (27) Afloat Technical Insertion (TI) units and (1) Ashore TI unit; with integration and associated costs for pre-installation design
and the installation of (5) Initial CANES Afloat units, (20) Afloat TI units and (1) Ashore TI unit that were procured in FY2026. Prior to FY2025, Agile Enclave (AE) was previously budgeted within the CANES
Afloat Technical Insertion (1.1.2) BKit Cost Element. Starting in FY25, AE procurements and installations are reflected in a separate Afloat BKit Cost Element (1.1.3 - Agile Enclave). In FY2027, (108) AE units are
planned for rapid procurement and deployment of AE capabilities across Naval platforms based on urgent and emerging Fleet needs. AE delivers capabilities in accordance with Joint Department of War priorities
supporting real world operations. Additional details on AE efforts are provided at a higher classification.

It is important to note that procurement quantities are the same CANES end item products referenced in CANES INTELL, LI 2925. Installation quantities represent sites receiving CANES also referenced in LI
2925. The associated dollars in this exhibit represent the non-Intel portion of the investment in the CANES system.




