 Justification:
 This funding is required to support General Purpose Electrical/Electronic Test Equipment (GPETE) and Calibration Standards (CALSTD) acquisition and modernization efforts. Modernization and replenishment
 of critical test equipment ensures measurement requirements are met and ready test equipment is available for fleet maintenance actions of ship/submarine systems. It provides calibration activities with the
 required capability to support fleet operational readiness needs and meet fleet self-sufficiency goals. All Navy systems and equipment are dependent upon being maintained by properly calibrated test equipment.
 Sailor safety and shipboard operations are impacted, including certifying reactor, steam plant, and combat systems. GPETE and CALIBRATION STANDARDS are priority readiness focus areas to support Sailor
 Quality of Service and Ready Ships.




