 Justification:
 Decrease to control from FY26 $7.852M to FY27 $3.523 is due to the completion of procurements of the equipment associated with the upgrades of test ranges to meet AN/ SLQ-32 (V)6 & (V)7 testing
 requirements and upgrades to various data links to ensure systems are fully mission capable for Fleet operations in FY26. FY27 funds include SESEF Program mission requirements to provide electromagnetic
 systems test and evaluation upgrades and modernization of afloat and shore commands to validate system performance following new construction and overhaul/availability and provides real-time assessment of
 material readiness in an operational environment.

 Funding for procurements and installations for upgrades and modernization of the eight operational sites and mobile trailers across the AORs to support the Shipboard Electronic Systems Evaluation Facility
 (SESEF). Increase of $4.78M from FY25 to FY26 is for procurement of testing equipment for the AN/SLQ-32 (V)6 & (V)7 upgrades at all fixed and mobile sites to ensure systems are fully mission capable for
 Fleet operations.




