 Justification:
 Increased funding in FY27 primarily supports Dual Band Radar (DBR) Engineering Change Proposal (ECP) efforts for Cyber security, failure reporting and tracking, Government technical software and Signal
 Data Processor (SDP) hardware installs in support of sustainment and OEM obsolescence efforts. FY27 funding increases for SPY-6 Family of Radars (FoR) to support System Equipment Sustainment and
 Technology Refresh for new SPY-6 platform deliveries to establish adequate infrastructure and sparing, along with a CVN 78 Radar Replacement GFE procurement in FY27 to support the replacement of the
 AN/SPY-3 and AN/SPY-4 radars. FY27 funding increases for SPEIR to support installs for the CRUDES and Shore Site systems being procured under PUs DC025 and DC000. FY27 funding increase for AN/
 SPQ-9B for the CVN 78 procurement, in addition to Design Services Allocation for CVN 78 planned AIT Installation. FY27 funds also increase with the addition of Littoral Combat System (LCS) funding being
 added to this budget to provide life cycle planning and infrastructure/configuration management, Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS), associated hardware and software
 obsolescence, logistics and engineering support for the AN/SPS-75 and AN/SPS-80 variants for the Freedom class and AN/SPS-77 variants for the Independence class.


