 Description:
 The budget reflects Scalable Modular Radio Clusters (SMRC) Multiband(MB) Radio Procurements, previously called "Integrated Waveform (IW) and Mobile User Objective System (MUOS)" capable systems.
 The budget reflects individual radio procurements and ancillary equipment procurements for surface, subsurface, and shore sites. For the SMRC MB variant, the required quantity of radios and ancillary
 equipment is dependent on the ship class configuration, or shore site configuration. Ancillary equipment includes power amplifiers, rack systems, human machine interface, and antennae upgrades or
 refurbishments.

 [SMRC Multiband Radio Procurement] Funding provides for the procurement and installation of Scalable Modular Radio Clusters (SMRC) Multiband Radio, previously called, Integrated Waveform (IW) and
 Mobile User Objective System (MUOS) systems. The system is a four-channel software defined radio that provides 19 satellite communications and Line of Sight (LOS) waveforms across the High Frequency
 (HF), Very High Frequency (VHF) and Ultra High Frequency (UHF) spectrum.

 FY2027 funding provides for procurement of four (4) SMRC Multiband radios with twenty (20) pieces of ancillary equipment for installation in FY 2029. FY2027 funding also provides for installation of six (6)
 SMRC Multiband Radios . These units were procured in FY 2025 for installation in FY 2027.




