 Justification:
 Total decrease from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is $5.470 million.

 FY 2027 request supports integration of afloat assets into cloud environment, expansion of Navy Exchange Point (NXP) to integrate with joint and tactical assets, and NSA connections for distributed Signals
 Intelligence (SIGINT) operations and includes funding provided for the extension of twelve DDGs.

 In FY 2027, Automated Digital Network System (ADNS) continues integration of Assured Command and Control capabilities to meet fleet requirements as well as fielding at Ashore sites. In FY 2027, ADNS
 funds are for the procurement of (30) Increment (INC) III Afloat units, (14) Ashore INC III units, (108) Agile Enclave (AE) units, (25) INC III Afloat Technical Insertion (TI) units, and (7) ADNS Advanced Networking
 Tactical System (ANTS) technical refreshes, with integration, and associated costs for pre-installation design. Additional increase in procurements are for ADNS INC III Ashore specifically for new Software
 Defined Networking (SDN) upgrades. Quantities for ADNS INC III Ashore decreased from (15) in FY26 to (14) in FY27 to decrease the number of sites supported. The FY 2027 procurements in AE and ADNS
 Ashore INC III are installed in the same FY.




