 Description:
 [P5 / NU019 Amphibious Communications]: Amphib Comms: Enhanced Position Location Reporting System - Data Radio (EPLRS-DR)/Enhanced Man-Pack UHF Tactical (EMUT) provides secure Anti-Jam (AJ),
 Ultra High Frequency (UHF) (420-450 MHz) and Line of Sight (LOS) data communications in support of amphibious operations at throughputs of up to 54 Kbps. EPLRS-DR provides embedded Position Location
 Information (PLI) between shipboard networks and the shore-based Marine Tactical Data Network (TDN) and the Army Tactical Internet (TI). Single Channel Ground and Airborne Radio System (SINCGARS)
 provides secure, anti-jam very high frequency (VHF) voice and data communications.

 Funding in FY27 includes procurement of 2 VRC-250 Upgrade Kit, 2 Tri-Band Antennas, and 3 Landing Force Iridium systems to be installed in FY28. Funding in FY27 also includes installation of 15 VRC-250
 Upgrade Kit, 4 Tri Band Antennas, 7 MUOS Functional Terminals, and 8 Landing Force Iridium systems that were procured in FY26.

 [P5 / NU020 Amphib Comms HFSAR]: High Frequency Shipboard Automatic Link Extension Radio (HFSAR) is a USMC support capability required on Amphibious platforms. HFSAR provides ship-to-mobile
 unit HF ALE capable system for rapid setup of critical LOS and over-the-horizon (OTH) communications in support of afloat and ashore intelligence and reconnaissance units. HFSAR provides a 2-channel HF
 Automatic Link Extension (ALE) capability aboard Amphibious class ships to support the embarked Marine Air-Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Commander by providing terrestrial, long-haul, ship-to-ship and ship-
 to-shore connectivity that is a critical Beyond Line of Sight (BLOS), over the-horizon (OTH), and Near Vertical Incidence Skywave (NVIS) warfighting requirement. This system is one of AC3 / Naval Tactical Grid
 systems formally specified by both Fleet Commanders as a threshold capability for global maritime command control and communications in a Distributed Maritime Environment to execute current warfighting
 plans.

 Funding in FY27 includes procurement of 5 HFSAR 2.0 upgrade kits to be installed in FY28. Funding in FY27 also includes installation of 5 HFSAR 2.0 upgrade kits for Marine Embarked Units (MEU), that were
 procured in FY26, to support HF/UHF communications between the Landing Force Operations Center (LFOC) and Marines ashore, and to ensure interoperability between the Navy and Marine Corps.




