INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0075$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$75$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 NU019 - Amphibious Communications (Amphib Comms): FY27 funding provides critical communications equipment to the USMC to meet afloat Command, Control, Communications, and Computers (C4)
 requirements. FY27 funding will provide Amphib Comms which includes Enhanced Position Location Radio System (EPLRS) Data Radio (DR), Mobile User Objective System (MUOS) Functional Terminal
 (MFT), Landing Force Iridium (LFI), Tri-Band Antenna upgrade, and Single Channel Ground and Airborne Radio System (SINCGARS). EPLRS and SINCGARS modernization aligns with the Navy's foundational
 priorities of readiness and capabilities as outlined in the Chief of Naval Operations 2022 Navigation Plan. Consolidating these systems under Amphib Comms will better allow the United States Navy to meet the
 requirements called out in the Afloat Marine Air Ground Task Force (MAGTF) C4 Required Capabilities Letter (AMC4RC) which calls out the major requirements of the USMC afloat in order to fight the battle from
 sea. These systems combined are integral in a Distributed Maritime Environment aboard Amphibious USN ships.

 Funding in FY27 includes procurement of 2 VRC-250 Upgrade Kit, 2 Tri-Band Antennas, and 3 Landing Force Iridium systems to be installed in FY28. Funding in FY27 also includes installation of 15 VRC-250
 Upgrade Kit, 4 Tri Band Antennas, 7 MUOS Functional Terminals, and 8 Landing Force Iridium systems that were procured in FY26.

 NU020 - HFSAR provides a 2-channel HF Automatic Link Extension (ALE) capability aboard Amphibious class ships to support the embarked Marine Air-Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Commander by providing
 terrestrial, long-haul, ship-to-ship and ship-to-shore connectivity that is a critical Beyond Line of Sight (BLOS), over the-horizon (OTH), and Near Vertical Incidence Skywave (NVIS) warfighting requirement. This
 system is one of AC3 / Naval Tactical Grid systems formally specified by both Fleet Commanders as a threshold capability for global maritime command control and communications in a Distributed Maritime
 Environment to execute current warfighting plans.

 Funding in FY27 includes procurement of 5 HFSAR 2.0 upgrade kits to be installed in FY28. Funding in FY27 also includes installation of 5 HFSAR 2.0 upgrade kits for Marine Embarked Units (MEU), that were
 procured in FY26, to support HF/UHF communications between the Landing Force Operations Center (LFOC) and Marines ashore, and to ensure interoperability between the Navy and Marine Corps.

 NU790 - Navy Expeditionary Command, Control, Communications, Computers, & Intelligence (C4I): Executes procurements for outfitting Table of Allowance (TOA) buy lists within the Naval Special Warfare
 (NSW) forces, ensuring common communications and Automated Data Processing (ADP) solutions are being coordinated, tracked, and procured. These procurements are critical to provide Deployable
 Distributed (D2) Command, Control & Communications (C3). FY27 funding provides mission critical communications equipment, to include one NSW variant Expeditionary Deployable Node (EDN), Global
 Broadcast System (GBS), portable handheld radios, man pack radios, secure satellite telephones, unmanned air vehicle (UAV) communication devices, and encryption-decryption devices to US Navy Sea, Air,
 and Land (SEAL) combat operations in forward deployed contingency locations. This equipment provides real-time, actionable, time-sensitive transmission and reception of mission orders, intelligence, action
 and engagement status reporting, imaging, and target specification simultaneously in multiple theaters throughout the world. The disaggregated nature of current operations has smaller SEAL Teams deployed
 across the Geographic Combatant Commanders (GCC) conducting combat or combat advise operations in austere environments with little-to-no established DoW infrastructure. This equipment supports NSW
 core mission requirements and is essential to the readiness and battlefield effectiveness of NSW in winning the current fight against extremist elements.




