INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0078$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$78$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 FY 2027 funding request for Commercial Broadband Satellite Program (CBSP) increased by $3.217M from FY 2026 to align with initial fielding of Satellite Terminal (transportable) Non-Geostationary (STtNG)
 Increment (Inc) 2 terminals (Qty 29), to include six (6) Military Sealift Command (MSC) ships, and procurement and installation of S-band capability on STtNG equipped ships. Funding supports installation of
 Wideband Anti-Jam Modem System (WAMS) modems (Qty 14).

 FY 2027 funding for Global Broadcast System (GBS) will have a net decrease of $3.576M. This includes a targeted increase to procure and install GBS Afloat Receive Terminals on more DDG platforms, aligning
 with ship modernization schedules and program capacity. The net decrease is due to the realignment of GBS Portable Receive Terminals from OPN BLI 3215 Satellite Communications Systems to OPN BLI 3057
 Communication Items Under $5M, to better support Naval Special Warfare (NSW) platforms. In FY 2027, the GBS program will procure six (6) Global Broadcast Systems (GBS).

 Starting in FY 2025, the CBSP program has updated its installation costs for STtNG terminals to reflect estimates based on historical actual cost data. The historical cost data is based on the last two (2) years of
 actual installation data. Increased estimates are attributed to greater than budgeted (~2%) inflation impacting material and labor rates, and changes to Ship Change Document (SCD) requirement specifications
 needed to address design changes and discrepancies found during pre-installation ship checks. Cost drivers include unanticipated extensions of production due to challenges such as procuring materials, system
 locations, or unforeseen services required. Prior estimates did not factor in sufficient risk for the uncertainty originating from forecasts based on component changes, installation services, cost increase impacts,
 and predecessor system installs data. The updated installation costs reflect cost realism based on the historical data by platform. STtNG Inc 2 will procure and field quantity 29 system in FY 2027. STtNG Inc
 2 consists of a wideband and protected system. Inc 2 fields the wideband Starlink system, Assured Command and Control (AC2) modem, PNT/GPNTS connections (optional), and the ALL.SPACE multibeam
 antenna. Inc 2 establishes a protected connection to additional LEO constellations (Kuiper) and adds MEO and GEO satellite constellations with additional ADNS links. Inc 2 aligns with DoW CIO direction to
 Title X Services to field hybrid terminals in response to Congressional Tasking.


