 Justification:
 FY27 decrease shows realignment of funds across the FYDP out of Navy to be placed in Air Force program requirements.

 The JCSE's Modernization Program is aligned with the DoWs efforts on Combined All Domain Command and Control (CJADC2) through resilient transport, resilient networking, and Zero-Trust. FY27 base
 funding procures capabilities for narrowband, wide band and protected satellite communications (SATCOM) terminals and systems, tactical radios, terrestrial communications systems, and satellite hubs. Funding
 also procures networking elements, virtual appliances, Video Teleconferencing (VTC) capabilities, alternative power solutions, airborne/en route, forced entry, cyber security, Denied, Degraded C2 Environments
 (D2C2E), and mobile joint C2 requirements. Advancements in technology, especially in commercial off-the-shelf solutions continue to provide opportunities to modernize JCSEs equipment sets with enhanced
 capabilities to support delayed/Disconnected Intermittent Low Bandwidth (DDIL) and zero trust capabilities with the smallest footprint, enhanced cyber security, reduced operations and maintenance costs and
 seamless integration with the Department of Defense Information Network (DODIN) and the Joint Information Environment (JIE).

 To consistently deliver state of the art technology solutions to meet emergent Combatant Command (CC) operational communications requirements, JCSE relies on the Modernization Program as outlined in
 Director, Joint Staff Memorandum (DJSM) 0148-20 whereby services are mandated to apportion and program procurement funds each year to support JCSE's Modernization Program. Per Defense Planning
 Guidance and DJSM 0148-20, the Navy agreed to fund JCSEs validated Modernization Program. JCSE's Modernization Program is based on CC and Service Components requirements and emerging
 technologies. The Services influence JCSEs spending plan through recommendations in concert with Major Defense Acquisition Program (MDAP) schedules, ensuring the Service investments meet Joint Service
 Requirements.

 Each year, JCSE produces an Annual Modernization Plan in compliance with the DJSM 0148-20 and JECC hosts a Semi-Annual Modernization Program Review for the Joint Staff, Services and CC
 representatives. The semi-annual program review provides transparency to all of DoW on the status of procurement and the projects that JCSE is working on. Each month, procurement status reports are
 submitted to United States Transportation Command, who holds overall responsibility for the JCSE Modernization Program.

 This line funds the Department of the Navy portion of the total JCSE Modernization Program. This program is jointly funded by Army, Navy, and Air Force.




