 Justification:
 The FY 2027 budget will procure the following:

 (2.1) Global Signal Analysis Laboratory (GSAL):
 - Funding sustains Signals Analysis Laboratories (SAL) integration for security and new technology requirements that facilitate technical analysis in diverse and contested electromagnetic environments. SALs are
 integral components of the Tech Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) Revitalization initiatives.

 (3.1.1) System Integration and Installation of Hardware (FIOC):
 - Funds provided for procurement and life cycle maintenance for Command/Control (C2) systems connected to Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI) networks. Funds will maintain a common baseline of
 analytical intelligence software tools.

 (4.1.1) Electronic Warfare (EW) Fleet Synthetic Trainer Consolidation:
 - Funds provided for Counter- Intelligence, Surveillance, Reconnaissance, Targeting (C-ISRT), Long-Range Fires and Live, Virtual, Constructive (LVC) Integrated Prioritized Capabilities Lists (IPCLs). This will
 give the ability to exercise shipboard Top Secret/Sensitive Compartmented Information (TS/SCI) capabilities in an environment not subject to counter-detection.

 (5.1.2) Tier 1 Life Cycle Management (LCM): FY27 funds ($0.030M) decrease due to reduction of tech refresh requirement

 (5.1.3) SIGINT / C-ISR Systems - Permanent Shipboard Installation: FY27 funds ($0.068M) decrease due to software and hardware LCM requirements.

 (5.1.4) SIGINT / C-ISR Systems- Life Cycle Management (LCM): FY27 funds ($0.018M) decrease due to software and hardware LCM requirements.

 (5.1.5) Fleet Training Wholeness (FTW): FY27 funds ($0.179M) decrease due to software and hardware LCM requirements.




