 Justification:
 Funding and inter-service agreements are used to procure Navy-Type/Navy-Owned (NT/NO) combat systems, support equipment, Integrated Logistics Support (ILS), certification, test and production support for
 United States Coast Guard (USCG) National Security Cutter (NSC), also known as the Maritime Security Cutter, Large (WMSL), the Offshore Patrol Cutter (OPC) Class, aka the Maritime Security Cutter, Medium
 (WMSM) and the Polar Security Cutter (PSC), aka the Maritime Security Cutter, Polar (WMSP), Fast Response Cutter (FRC), aka the Patrol Coastal Cutter (WPC), the Arctic Security Cutter (ASC) and the 270'
 Medium Endurance Cutter (WMEC) modernization effort being constructed under the Coast Guard's Surface Acquisition Program. Funding also supports Command, Control, Communications, Computers, and
 Intelligence (C4I) systems and associated logistic support for the Offshore Patrol Cutter. These efforts are ongoing.

 FY 2027 funding is provided for AN/SPQ-9B ILS for WMSLs; procure Identification, Friend or Foe (IFF) AN/APX-123(V) equipment, ILS and certification support for WPCs; procure IFF equipment and ILS support
 for WMSMs and WPCs; procure MK 53 Decoy Launching System (DLS) for WMSMs; procure the MK 20 Electro-Optical Sensor System (EOSS) and provide ILS/test support for WMSMs; provide combat system
 integration support for WMSLs, WPCs, PSCs and WMSMs; procure the Multi-mode Radar (MMR) for the WMSM program; procure ATHENA Control, Correlation & Display (CCD) System for WMSMs and provide
 combat system integration of the Technical Insertion TI-16 Common Display System and integration support for the ATHENA Control Correlation and Display (CCD) System.

 Program Executive Office Command, Control, Communications, Computers, and Intelligence (PEO C4I) FY 2027 funding is provided for the procurement of Navy Type Navy Owned (NT/NO) Command, Control,
 Communications, Computers, and Intelligence (C4I) equipment on National Security Cutter (NSC), Offshore Patrol Cutter (OPC) and Patrol Security Cutter (PSC) class ships to include: Cryptography (Crypto) -
 Qty 2; Command & Control Processor (C2P) - Qty 2; ARC-210 Radios & Amps - Qty 24; OE-570 Ultra High Frequency Satellite Communications (UHF SATCOM) Antenna System - Qty 1; OA-9277A Ultra High
 Frequency (UHF) Coupler - Qty 2 and Multi-Functional Information Distribution (MIDS) On-Ship Modernization (MOS MOD) - Qty 1.".




