 Description:
 Minotaur Family of Services (MFoS) provides overarching stewardship to the Minotaur Enterprise by providing Software ("Minotaur Core"), Data Distribution ("Labyrinth"), and Training.

 Minotaur is platform-agnostic Government software framework consisting of interfaces, data management, sensor exploitation, multi-source/platform correlation/fusion, and displays built to support Tasking,
 Collection, Processing, Exploitation, and Dissemination (TCPED) of sensor data. It creates a common tactical picture that provides data dissemination and interoperability methods within the Naval Operational
 Architecture (NOA) framework to support a Naval integrated kill chain for Distributed Maritime Operations (DMO).

 Minotaur is the foundation of the Minotaur Family of Services (MFoS) architecture which is the sole Program of Record (PoR) for the Tri-Service Enterprise (USN, USMC and USCG). MFoS capabilities are
 integrated across the maritime services (e.g., platforms and command centers) in support of the Tri-Service Maritime Strategy, Advantage at Sea. Minotaur operates at the Controlled Unclassified Information
 (CUI), Secret (S), and Top Secret (TS)/Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI) security levels. Within MFoS, a Data Distribution architecture ("Labyrinth") aggregates tactical Minotaur data with national data
 to provide data-lake, data-warehousing, and data-dissemination using standard protocols via web-based services or Internet Protocol (IP) based networks to the tactical edge and disadvantaged users for two-
 way, one-way, and Emissions Control (EMCON) operations.

 This effort includes the procurement and delivery of data distribution capabilities to Fleet Commanders, as well as Technical Data Packages (TDPs) supporting ISR&T capabilities, to include TCPED of airborne,
 afloat and ashore systems across the Department of War (DoW) and Department of Homeland Security (DHS).




