 Justification:
 The Systems Replacement and Modernization (SRAM) funds fleet priorities for modernization efforts at Naval training ranges in support of fleet training wholeness (FTW). Projects are non-recurring efforts that
 vary from year to year and are prioritized on an annual basis to meet fleet training readiness requirements. SRAM ensures current fleet training capabilities are not degraded for the lack of minor equipment.

 The ACAT IV Undersea Warfare Training Ranges (USWTR) Program of Record (PoR) contract was awarded 8 July 21 for $410M and continues the effort to modernize and deliver six (6) Training Ranges. The
 In-Water Sensor (IWS) system and shore electronics for Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW) training ranges at Pacific Missile Range Facility (PMRF), Barking Sands, HI, (e.g. Barking Sands Tactical Underwater
 Range (BARSTUR)/Barking Sands Underwater Range Expansion (BSURE) and Southern California ASW Range (SOAR), CA). The effort will be a time-phased procurement exception to the full funding policy.
 Hardware buys will vary in cost from year to year to meet the Fleet's required date for Initial Operational Capability (IOC) which is slated for BARSTUR/BSURE (4QFY2027) and Tanner Bank (TB) (4QFY2030).
 Full Operational Capability (FOC) is slated for San Clemente Island (SCI) (4QFY2031) and SOAR (4QFY2032). FY2027 procurements include funds for SCI IWS procurement, production, and test, SOAR trunk
 and internode cable procurement, and Display, Processing and Control System (DPCS) TB/SCI procurement, production, test and integration with IWS efforts and DPCS BARSTUR/BSURE final analysis and
 closeout actions to declare IOC. Additionally, this effort funds various Systems Engineering Technical Reviews required to execute the Undersea Warfare Training Range Increment II and III programs.

 Funds in FY2027 will continue Full-Rate Production of Tactical Combat Training System Increment II (TCTS II) and continues efforts to field additional participant systems, ground subsystems and remote range
 units. FY2027 funds the procurement of one (1) Common Ground Subsystem (CGS), four (4) Remote Range Units (RRU) to provide encryption capability for Fleet training exercises.

 SC105 EW Electronic Warfare (EW) Threat Presentation funding fluctuates from year to year reflecting Navy prioritization of various EW Threat Presentation devices for use at multiple Tactical Training Range
 (TTR) sites, including Fallon, NV; Yuma, AZ; Southern California Tactical Training Range (SCTTR), CA; Townsend, SC; Mid-Atlantic Electronic Warfare Range (MAEWR), NC. FY2027 Fleet Training Wholeness
 Initiative procures additional ALQ-167 Electronic Attack pods, EW 5th GEN Modular Remote Threat Emitter (MRTE) Tier 1 & Tier 2 Systems, and completes specific number of electronic warfare system
 technology refreshes based on available budget to sustain and improve availability and maintainability of secure authority to operate (ATO) cyber certifications for initial ATO's at Fleet range sites that include EW
 Opposition Force (OPFOR) training capabilities and connect those systems to the Navy Enterprise Tactical Training Network (NETTN).

 Funds in FY2027 for Live-Virtual-Constructive (LVC) will provide equipment for additional distributed mission training capability to East Coast and West Coast Tactical Training Ranges (TTR), with voice
 communication and datalink equipment in support of Live Virtual Constructive (LVC) capabilities. Install distributed network capabilities at various West Coast TTR's, according to Fleet priorities, in support of LVC
 capabilities.




