 Justification:
 Expeditionary Airfields (EAF) -FY 2027 Expeditionary Airfields funding is required for procurement of EAF Surfacing Equipment, Lighting Equipment, Arresting Gear and associated support costs. VTOL AAP
 funding is required to procure updated surfacing components and material that enable the war fighter to install and support VTOL operations. Procurement of AM2 matting will continue to be the Airfield Surfacing
 Solution for main runways and sustainment airfields along with Dual Cone Penetrometer ECP and F70 ECP for complimentary airfield installation equipment. Lighting ALS, RLS, LED Airfield and Lighting
 Optimization ECPs address the obsolescence and reliability of the currently utilized aging legacy system as well as the CAT I Instrument Flight Rules and Night Vision Device. Additionally, the M31 Expeditionary
 Arresting Gear provides modernization and replacement of the legacy M31 arresting gear currently facing obsolescence issues.

 Aircraft Rearming Equipment - FY 2027 baseline funding is required for HLU-288/E/HLU-196 Bomb Hoist Replacement, and associated support costs.

 Aircraft Launch and Recovery Equipment (ALRE) -

 Information Systems - MA: FY 2027 Marine Aviation funding is required for installation costs of hardware for Moriah Wind Systems ECPs and associated support costs. The ALRE Amphibious Assault Ship
 (AAS) Information Systems provides modernization of state-of-the-art wind measuring equipment, boundary defense capability and resiliency providing cyber secure operationally available aviation networks.


