 Description:
 This budget line item funds the procurement for Advanced Arresting Gear (AAG) life cycle support modifications and upgrades required aboard Ford Class Carriers, Jet Car Track Site (JCTS) and Runway
 Arrested Landing Site (RALS) systems, and AAG Depot. Modifications included in the budget support fatigue life, obsolescence and performance enhancements to ensure the system remains operational
 throughout the life of the program. AAG replaces Mark 7 arresting gear aboard Ford Class aircraft carriers and provides the U.S. Navy with the ability to recover existing and projected aircraft carrier based tail-
 hook equipped air vehicles well into the 21st century. AAG enhances operational capability, provides increased operational availability, reduces manning, maintenance and support costs. AAG is currently
 installed and deployed aboard CVN-78, installed aboard CVN-79, and installed in two land-based test sites JCTS and RALS.

 Prior Years ($76.9M) funded under Aircraft Support Equipment (BLI 4213 and BLI 4216).




