 Justification:
 FY 2027 Baseline funding is required for Depot Standup and modifications based on obsolescence. Work categories include Production Engineering (PE), Integrated Logistics Support (ILS), and Non-Recurring
 Engineering (NRE).

 Depot Standup Support Equipment is to procure equipment required for initial standup of EMALS depot level repair capabilities for Ford Class ships. This includes final procurement of logistics products,
 procurement of on-equipment tooling, test fixtures, test stands, and OEM manufactured tooling to support upcoming planned overhaul periodicities. Increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 supports the development
 and delivery of Support Equipment Recommendation Data (SERDs) and Detailed Functional Description Data Packages (DFDDPs) to support the design and procurement of test benches for high power and low
 power testing, troubleshooting, and fault diagnostic capability for component repair. Software Support Activity (SSA) Support Equipment is required to make minor improvements and expand capabilities of the
 existing EMALS lab. Standup of EMALS Depot and SSA are required to establish the capability and capacity to support four Ford Class ships by 2028.

 Modifications to fielded ships are required in order to retrofit obsolescence solutions identified in New Construction efforts and ensure support for all Ford Class ships. This involves any NRE to adapt the New
 Construction solution to existing hulls, kits, and installations. These efforts include, but are not limited to, EMALS Rectifier Temperature Transmitter Obsolescence (ECP-I-EMALS-0075).

 Other EMALS Obsolescence Modifications funding is required to incorporate changes based on emergent obsolescence/tech refresh within EMALS. Funds may address ECPs due to Technical Directives (TDs)
 which are required to support the incorporation of established capability, reliability, maintainability, obsolescence, safety, and supportability improvements.

 Notes for Installation Schedule:
 1. Installations are subject to change with ship availability schedule updates.
 2. The year-to-year unit installations costs will vary and can exceed the projected yearly inflation rate due to the hardware installation cost being dependent on quantity and location of the ship at the time of install
 or which site is
 being updated, which CVN, and the ships baseline configuration.
 3. Production lead time includes pre-installation checkout, kitting with other installation hardware and drawings, and time to deliver the hardware to the installation site.

 Non-Recurring Engineering (NRE) funding levels fluctuate due to a mix and complexity of system Engineering Change Proposals (ECP) written and verified in each year. All ECPs do not require the same level of
 NRE.


