 Justification:
 The FY27 budget increases by $24.307M from FY26 to FY27 due to additional funding for MDCX product Support, UMCS Integration of Ford Class Advanced Arresting Gear (AAG) and Electromagnetic Aircraft
 Launch System, Obsolescence Engineering, Integration of Deferred Supportability Requirements and C4I integration. This funding will be used for nonrecurring engineering to perform engineering change
 proposals to correct deficiencies or address obsolescence issues and will provide essential OEM support for installation and initial system operations. This investment is necessary to ensure the continued
 reliability and modernization of the GCS.

 In FY2027 UMCS will fund the following:

 CVN B
 - Prepare for installation of the UAWC Fan Room modification and Final Deployment Configuration (FDC) modification in the FY28 Docking Planned Incremental Availability (DPIA).
 - Prepare for installation of MQ25 work centers and ready room installation during FY28 DPIA.
 - Procure tech refresh equipment for installation during the FY28 DPIA.

 CVN C
 - Commence MQ25 work centers and ready room installation during FY27 Planned Incremental Availability (PIA).
 - Procure MD-5C variant AVP consoles for installation during FY27 PIA.
 - Remove temporary AVP consoles and replace with MQ-5C variant, shock-qualified consoles to support second CVN test.
 - Commence ADMACS ECP installation during FY27 PIA.
 - Support post installation discrepancies to perform C4I operational network evaluations.
 - Procure tech refresh equipment and install during the FY27 PIA.
 - Procure long lead material to support Phase 1 of the Navy Modernization Process to support installation during the FY30 DPIA.

 CVN D
 - Procure Block 2 hardware upgrade kit, comprising the Final Deployment Configuration (FDC), for installation during the FY29 Planned Incremental Availability (PIA), to support AWOTF.
 - Continue installation of the MD-5C and MQ25 work centers and ready room that began in the FY26 DPIA.
 - Continue installation of ADMACS ECP that began in the FY26 DPIA.
 - Procure tech refresh equipment for installation during FY29 PIA.

 CVN E
 - Commence FY27 Initial Deployment Configuration (IDC) Increment 2 Installation. This configuration capitalizes on work performed in prior years when MD-5A was planned and is an evolutionary step to enable
 Deployment of MQ-25.



