 Justification:
 The FY 2026 funding for Strategic Missile Systems Equip includes $491,179 thousand of discretionary and $9,180 thousand of mandatory funding for a total of $500,359 thousand. The mandatory funds include
 procurement of both hardware and related software of non-tactical IT equipment and supports the acceleration of the development, procurement, and integration of the Nuclear-Armed Sea-Launched Cruise
 Missile program (SLCM-N). Further information for this reconciliation request is provided in Section 20008 (Nuclear) of the One Big Beautiful Bill Act spend plan.

 OTHER MATERIAL SUPPORT
 A broad range of other material support equipment must be procured for deployed SSBNs, shore installations and contractor facilities. Included within this category are general and special purpose test
 equipment, launcher expendables, navigation principal items, test instrumentation in support of missile flight tests, and missile checkout equipment. Amounts included within this category are subdivided as
 follows:

 Launcher and Handling Equipment:
 Cost Codes 1.1 and 1.2 provide for Gas Generator (GG) Production and GG Case Hardware. GGs are utilized to eject Trident II (D5) missiles from the missile tubes during a launch.

 Cost Code 1.1 FY 2027 Funding increase due to the procurement of 23 Gas Generators to support Sea leg capacity expansion, an increase from 0 in FY 2026. The production unit cost for these generators has
 been adjusted upward to account for inflationary impacts and realized increases in material and production costs from the industrial base.

 Cost Code 1.2 funding provides the procurement and qualification of GG Case Hardware required to replace cases for expended/fired GGs. Funding in this category fluctuates year to year due to flight schedules.
 FY 2027 decreases due to the quantity of gas generator hardware decreasing to 10, PreLoading Indicating (PLI) Washer decreasing to 0.

 Cost Code 1.3 FY 2027 decrease due to the procurement of 3 Ballast Transport Fixtures (BTFs) from 6 in FY 2026.

 Fire Control Equipment:
 Cost Code 2.1 funding provides for procurement of continued capital maintenance projects at the Naval Industrial Reserve Ordnance Plant (NIROP) in Pittsfield, MA. The Navy NIROP facility in Massachusetts is
 a large multi dwelling facility, encompassing almost 900,000 sq. ft. There are three main ordnance plant (OP) buildings on the NIROP facility, OPs 1, 2, and 3. The OPs were built in the 1940s and 1950s, and the
 last major renovations were in the 1970s. Funding fluctuates annually based on specific maintenance projects necessary to correct environmental, safety, and energy conservation deficiencies. FY 2027 scope
 includes OP1 Air Handler Refresh and OP3 Load Center Replacement. Electrical Load Centers at the Pittsfield NIROP are large, integrated critical systems that combine a transformer, switchgear, and a breaker
 box into a single housing.

 Cost Code 2.2 FY 2027 increase is due to a full redesign of the Missile Simulator Interface (MSI) and the Missile Interface Test Module (MITM) Module for Training Stimulation System (TSS) and the Weapon
 System Simulator (WSS). MSI and MITM support the fleet training TSS and troubleshooting and validation of tactical systems WSS. Without these modules the fleet cannot be supported for missile interface
 testing and validation.

