INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0111$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$111$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 VN077 Navy EOD Equipment - FY 2027 funding for Navy EOD Equipment supports the modernization and advancement of Naval EOD capabilities through procurement. Obsolete and aging equipment will be
 replaced with advanced tools and equipment specific to operational scenarios as well as future threats. Continued procurement of Spectral Radiation Monitors (SRM-50) replaces legacy monitoring systems
 for EOD forces to maintain mission effectiveness and operational relevance to combatant commanders. The current capability does not enable Navy EOD Forces to effectively support their counter weapons
 of mass destruction mission. The Timed Firing Device (TFD) allows for precise detonation at fixed times set in the field, as well as programmed times set in advance of operations, reducing the chance of early
 detonation before the EOD technician can reach a safe standoff distance, while simultaneously allowing EOD operations in communications denied environment. Competitive production contract award for the
 Timed Firing Device will enable scaling of production to meet joint requirements compared to low rate initial production capacity.

 VN870 JOINT CREW - FY 2027 supports procurement of engineering changes to the fielded JCREW I1B1 systems that are necessary to implement advanced countermeasure capabilities against the global
 Radio Controlled IED (RCIED).

 CUAS/DRAKE - FY 2027 qty increase of 108 units in FY 2026 to 326 units in FY 2027 due to additional $26.7M for Drake Systems to meet the Military Sealift Command (MSC) required inventory objective. The
 increase in FY 2027 is also due to the procurement of more complete Drake systems to complete outfitting of Ships.

 VN790 DRAKE Combat Operations NAVCENT: $26.2M of FY 2025 Supplemental funding from Israel Security Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2024 (Division A of Public Law 118-50) for the procurement of
 DRAKE Combat Operations NAVCENT.




