 Footnotes:
 (1)
   Integrated Logistic Support (ILS)/Production Support - Government capability to perform repairs on system components that have failed during shipboard operations, provide Government Failure Reporting Analysis and Corrective Action
 System (FRACAS) support, and obtain the hardware and software maintenance required to continuously operate the system.
 (2)
   Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs) - Address previously known, emergent, and anticipated reliability and other Fleet generated emergent issues. ECPs were awarded for Non-Recurring Engineering (NRE) costs associated with the
 engineering changes for system components due to obsolescence of critical parts and technology.
 (3)
       Spares - Procurement of long lead time spares and repair parts for critical system components that address onboard failures.
 (4)
   Tech Refresh - Support of Government components developed in prior years that will be replaced by available (newer) components/sub-systems and will update the configuration infrastructure necessary to maintain operational readiness
 and improve system performance.




