 Justification:
 The overall FY2027 budget decreased in value as compared to FY2026. The budget supports Undersea Warfare requirements. FY2027 adds funding for procurement and delivery of Columbia Class trainer
 equipment. This budget will allow the ability to support crew certification and deployment events for Columbia readiness.

 TD 300 NAVIGATION TRAINERS -

 3.1 NAVIGATION SAFETY OF SHIP TRAINERS- FY2027 procures two modernization kits to update the Submarine Bridge Trainer for Navigation Training. TYCOM requirement. In addition, starting in FY27, this
 line includes 3.2) SSBN SAFETY OF SHIP TRAINERS due to the procurement and final delivery of the trainers resulting in the trainers shifting to modernization and tech refresh cycle.

 TD 500 ATTACK CENTER TRAINERS

 5.4 COLUMBIA SMMTT EPM - new requirement starting FY2027 to support the Engineering Production Model for Columbia Class training to support crew certification and Demonstration and Shakedown
 Operation (DASO) training as directed by the Fleet.




