 CVN 78 Class Training Equipment
 FY27 increase of $0.688M supports the planned increase in Technical Training Equipment (TTE) requirements of new CVN 78 Class Contractor Furnished Equipment (CFE) systems.

 LCAC Life Cycle Training System
 FY27 decrease ($1.449M) for SSC/LCAC Life Cycle Training procurement is due to completion of the LCAC legacy trainer modernization in FY26.

 FY27 increase of $52.524M for P5 Surface Training Device Modifications in accordance with the Surface Training Investment Plan (STIP) requirements for the fiscal year. Increase due to significant planned
 investments to include CE 2.1.1 SURFACE MINOR MODS for STP Combat Systems Engineering training devices and tech refresh for FY27. This program provides funding to procure, modify, and upgrade
 training devices to keep them compatible with equivalent changes made to Fleet operational equipment. Funds ensure alignment between Surface Learning Centers and Fleet Concentration Area training
 systems and Fleet training requirements as dictated by the Surface Training Investment Plan (STIP).

 Increase in support of procurements for At-Sea LVC capability for DDG 1000 as well as Integration of Naval Strike Missile onto FFG 62 LVC embedded training capability.

 Ready Relevant Learning (RRL)

