 Justification:
 Funding increase of $15.843M from FY26 to FY27 Supports:
 The increase in OPN funding transitions multiple new Joint Petroleum Over the Shore (JPOTS) Family of Systems (FoS) capabilities to production, procuring the initial units for the Distributed Littoral Operations
 Fuel Transfer System (DLOFTS), Amphibious Bulk Liquid Transfer System-JPOTS (ABLTS-J), and Reach From The Beach (RFTB) system. This increase also initiates the Towable Fuel Systems (TFS) program.
 The overall funding line continues to support the ongoing production of the Seabased Petroleum Distribution System (SPDS).




