 Justification:
 8101 Justifications

 FY27 funds ($257.4M) increase to procure and employ up to five Multi-Domain Training Support Vessels (TSVs), eight station Combat Control training system devices and meet operational, support,
 maintenance, and safety requirements. These assets address critical shortfalls of fixed tactical training ranges, provides AN/BYG-1 and AN/BQQ-10 tactical software currently employed onboard submarines and
 accomplish the Accession Modernization training efforts for ND (Navy Diver).

 1.1 [USFFC] LIFE CYCLE MANAGEMENT (LCM) - FY27 ($0.804M) increase due to hardware and software procured in FY26 required within the Navy Continuous Training Environment (NCTE).

 1.2 [USFFC] BALLISTIC MISSILE DEFENSE (BMD) - FY27 ($0.694M) increase due to increase of software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.3 [USFFC] BALLISTIC MISSILE DEFENSE (BMD) FLEET SYNTHETIC TRAINING (FST) at Sea - FY27 funds ($0.052M) increase due to software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.4 [USFFC] ANTI-ACCESS AREA DENIAL (A2AD) -FY27 funds ($0.081M) increase due to software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.5 through 1.6 N/A

 1.7 [USFFC] NAVAL INTEGRATED FIRE CONTROL - COUNTER AIR (NIFC-CA) - FY27 funds ($0.226M) increase due to software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.8 [USFFC] INTEGRATED MARITIME PORTABLE ACOUSTIC SCORING AND SIMULATION (IMPASS) SYSTEM - FY27 funds ($0.527M) decrease due to even-numbered FY funding for phased replacement
 of Integrated Maritime Portable Acoustic Scoring and Simulation (IMPASS) system.

 1.9 [USFFC] LVC FLEET TRAINING WHOLENESS (FTW) - FY27 funds ($1.589M) increase due to Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements in FY26 investments.

 1.10 [USFFC] EAST COAST TRAINING NETWORK CONSOLIDATION - FY27 funds ($1.864M) increase due to expansion software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.11 [USFFC] WEST COAST TRAINING NETWORK CONSOLIDATION - FY27 funds ($0.695M) increase due to software and hardware Life Cycle Management (LCM) requirements.

 1.12 N/A

 1.13 [USFFC/ CSG4] TRAINING SUPPORT VESSEL (TSV) PROCUREMENT & SUSTAINMENT - FY27 ($0.150M) decrease system procurement completed in FY26. Amount reduced for transition sustainment.

