 Justification:
 Fleet SCI IT: Funding enables continued network and storage equipment sustainment and modernization for the Naval Intelligence community. Funding enables continued network and storage equipment
 sustainment and modernizes SCI coalition network enclaves on force level ships and the Maritime Operations Centers (MOCs).

 ONI RED (CR): Program terminated. Funding is used to finance long-term investments for the procurement, production and modernization of satellite communications and electronics equipment required for the
 sensitive sensor tracking capabilities hosted on LYNX (G5) Mobile User Objective System (MUOS) Ground Station Infrastructure platform systems. The program must acquire and configure advanced LYNX
 (G5) MUOS satellite communications processing system and sensors components to meet advanced capabilities in support of maritime tracking requirements for US Navy platforms, unmanned systems and
 Intelligence Community directorates, in for every Combatant Commands (COCOM).




