INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0142$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$142$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 Net increase between FY26 and FY27 is $37.892M. FY27 plans are as follows:

 -Network Management funding supports critical NEN CONUS and OCONUS hardware and software compliance based technical refreshes to network performance while modernized capabilities are being
 transformed and will slow down the rapid rate of technical debt accumulation that continues to compound year over year. Funding supports reducing the risk of network vulnerabilities and improving resiliency
 for the warfighter at High Interest sites with transport and boundary upgrades , continued migration toward a unified shore and tactical edge afloat network, integration and expansion of the mobile platform, and
 implementation of a technical enterprise architecture that replaces obsolete technologies associated with the CONUS and OCONUS platforms.

 FY27 increase ($13.149M) is driven by investment upgrades for critical network infrastructure that is End-of-Life, obsolete, and unsupported by the original manufacturer. Replacing critical Technical Debt
 that has surpassed End-of-Life enables the Naval Enterprise Network to migrate towards a modern information ecosystem architecture with upgraded, resilient infrastructure to meet the needs of modern day
 information warfare by delivering and maintaining a real-time Cyber Ready posture that implements Zero Trust and securely moves data from anywhere to anywhere via agnostic network transport in alignment
 with the Chief of Naval Operations for Information Warfare Navy Blueprint.

 -Cybersecurity supports NMCI hardware and software compliance based technical refresh to pace the obsolescence-based cyber security threat until replaced by Network Transformation and modernization
 efforts. Funds provided will continue engineering, integration, and implementation for replacement of DISA's Endpoint Security Solution (formerly Host Based Security System (HBSS)), existing Cisco and Trellix
 Intrusion Prevention System (IPS) sensors, Assured Compliance Assessment Solution (ACAS) for infrastructure expansion (i.e., add additional servers) and Department of Defense Zero Trust Strategy developed
 under section 1528 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2022. FY27 increase ($0.276M) is due to inflation.

 -Information Transport funding will continue to eradicate technical debt for unclassified and classified transport boundaries to include the technical refresh modernization program of NEN CONUS and OCONUS
 networks by replacing 450 100M KG-175D with 1GB encryption device to alleviate the legacy latent SIPR bandwidth issues, and complete enterprise transport implementations to buy down end of life equipment
 to include Certificate Logon (CLO) enforcement and hardware warranty for new hardware implemented in SMIT Development and Baseline Labs. FY27 increase ($0.253M) is due to inflation.

 -Cloud Services refreshes on-premise infrastructure in order to offer capabilities like Teams and SharePoint Online. Funds provided will continue Classified and Unclassified NMCI Voice/Video over Internet
 Protocol (VVoIP) Cryptographic Login (CLO) infrastructure upgrades to include design, hardware and software procurement, and implementation of mandated CLO requirement for NMCI VVoIP infrastructure.
 FY27 increase ($0.064M) is due to inflation.

 -Transformation funding will minimize the distance between the user and cloud services by continuing to invest in critical infrastructure requirements defined in the DoW Sec IL6 and Nautilus Agile Release
 Trains, improving computing and storage capacity with Flank Speed Edge Azure deployments that reduce operation and management complexity while increasing security, availability and resiliency of the
 network and deliver a modern end user experience. Strategic Flank Speed Edge deployments will enable future reductions in non-IT infrastructure expenses by reducing the Naval IT footprint across the
 Enterprise. The Network Product Group will realize improved transport by reducing hairpins and cutting over rehomed edge sites to existing Naval Exchange Points (NXP) while procuring critical hardware for two
 (2) OCONUS sites. A Base Area Network (BAN)/Local Area Network (LAN) redesign will continue to move towards bringing "any data, any time" to the warfighter and a data backup/resiliency solution will ensure



