INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0144$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$144$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 The FY 2027 request supports essential spare and repair parts required to sustain fleet readiness, enable modernization efforts, and ensure the Navy can meet operational demands across all maritime and
 aviation platforms. Recent funding levels required the Navy to prioritize the most critical strategic deterrence, surface warfare, and aviation systems, ensuring continuity of operations for Ohio-class submarines,
 AEGIS combat systems, CIWS, SPY-6 radar, and Ford-class carrier launch and recovery systems. The FY 2027 investment builds on these priorities by restoring balanced support across the broader Fleet,
 including surface combatants, expeditionary forces, CVNs, amphibious platforms, and emerging modernization efforts such as LPD Flight II, DDG upgrades, NC3 systems, and key HM&E improvements. This
 funding enables the Navy to align spare-parts inventories with updated readiness models, support ongoing installations of cross-platform systems such as CANES, and meet outfitting and lay-in requirements for
 new and modernized ships. The FY 2027 request ensures the Fleet remains ready, resilient, and capable of meeting national defense objectives.

 The FY2027 base investments of $766M support increased outfitting surface spares funding based on refreshed readiness models for SWE critical systems for both surface combatants, expeditionary force units,
 and CVNs. These requirements are in addition to the initial, outfitting and lay-in requirements already existing for all platforms including EOD, Mine Countermeasures, submarine strategic deterrence outfitting,
 critical Nuclear Command, Control and Communications (NC3), SLQ-32, LPD Midlife LHA/D modernization, and first LPD FLT II ship, DDG Modernization, and AEGIS SPY 6 Advanced Radar System, MK 41
 VLS, upgrades for DDG 51 Class HM&E.

 INITIAL/OUTFITTING/LAY-IN Spares (9020-10-20-70)

 J0200 / Surface Combatant HM&E - $0.861 million increase for DDG 51 Arleigh Burke-class destroyers the Fleet's most heavily tasked multi mission combatants, funding will be used to execute FY26 Surface
 Combatant HM&E tech refresh requirements including the DDG 51 Integrated Bridge Navigation System (IBNS) Tech Refresh, Machinery Control System (MCS) Tech Refresh, Engineering Control (EC) Tech
 Refresh, and Repair Station Console (RSC) Tech Refresh to ensure these systems are fully supported with the installation/lay in spares and onboard repair parts required during DDG Modernization availabilities.
 These upgrades directly support the Navy's requirement for safe navigation, reliable ship control, and resilient command and control in high threat environments, which is essential given the heightened
 operational tempo and the near daily missile, UAV, and proxy activity our deployed destroyers are encountering in the Middle East.

 J0670 / Other Navigation Equipment - $5.455 million request, no program growth. Line had $0.0M in FY26 discretionary spending.

 J0840 / Sub Periscope, Imaging and Supt Equipment - $0.287 million increase is a result of Reconciliation. The FY 2026 budget for Sub Periscope, Imaging and Supt Equip SUBLI 10 included $0.0M of
 discretionary funding. As a result, the FY 2027 budget for SUBLI 10 is a net increase of $287K from the FY 2026 total budget which consists of $0M in discretionary and $147K in mandatory (reconciliation)
 funding. FY 2027 funding will procure Lay-In spares and Inventory Augmentation for the Submarine Imaging, Electronic Warfare, and RADAR modernizations to all classes of submarines.

 J0840 / Sub Periscope, Imaging and Supt Equipment - $35.814 million increase is a result of Reconciliation. The FY 2026 budget for Sub Periscope, Imaging and Supt Equip SUBLI 10 included $0.0M of
 discretionary funding. As a result, the FY 2027 budget for SUBLI 10 is a net increase of $35.814M from the FY 2026 total budget which consists of $0M in discretionary and $9.531M in mandatory (reconciliation)
 funding. FY 2027 funding will procure On Board Repair Parts, Installation and Checkout Spares, and depot stock for Submarine Imaging, Electronic Warfare, and RADAR modernizations to all classes of
 submarines. The initial spares requirement and deployment load out is calculated via an OPNAV approved readiness based sparing model that identifies the minimum sparing level required to achieve USN
 mandated Operational Availability.

