 Description:
 Family of Anti-Armor Weapon Systems (FOAAWS)

 The Family of Anti-Armor Weapon Systems (FOAAWS) portfolio supports multiple anti-armor weapons and training devices. FOAAWS includes the Multi-purpose Anti-Armor Anti-Personnel Weapon System
 (MAAWS) M3A1's upgraded Fire Control System - 14 (FCS 14), which is a precision-mounted optic with integrated Laser Range finder and a ballistic computer to provide precision firing solutions based on
 ammo type, range, and other key targeting information for MAAWS engagements. Training devices required to support initial training at formal schools, operational training at operational units, and unit-level
 sustainment support equipment include: 7.62mm and 20mm Sub-caliber Adapters used for familiarization and operational training for the MAAWS, as well as the M72AS Light Anti-Tank Weapon (LAW) Trainer
 and the M287 AT4 Practice Launcher. These programs provide anti-armor, anti-personnel, anti-materiel, and assault capabilities and training materiel to Marine Rifle Squads, Combat Engineers, Reconnaissance
 Teams, and Marine Corps Forces Special Operations Command to effectively execute both offensive and defensive operations.




